  "texts": [
    "• The third cost function, named as the supervised fake news loss, is used to directly optimize the task of detecting fake news.",
    "To achieve this, FANG generates an embedding for each news article by combining both the article's own embedding and the embedding of the news source that has published it.",
    "FANG can be trained rapidly and enables predictions to be made on new data without requiring the entire graph to be re-processed.",
    "Rumor detection methods commonly utilize text semantics and propagation structure to automatically classify rumors.",
    "However, they often overlook the impact of false or irrelevant interactions within the propagation structure, leading to reduced accuracy."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}